{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"msg_xefzkcsjyggpg6jsdbwf6","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"851887833","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/private/tmp/tokenwarden-bench/claude-code/2026-07-21T17-57-52-415Z/tokenwarden-docs-from-code-2/repo/bench-artifacts/cache-api.md","content":"# Cache API\n\nA simple in-memory cache implementation.\n\n## createCache()\n\nCreates a new cache instance with support for storing and retrieving key-value pairs.\n\n**Returns:** An object with `get`, `set`, `delete`, and `clear` methods.\n\n### Example\n\n```javascript\nconst cache = createCache()\n```\n\n## Methods\n\n### get(key)\n\nRetrieves a value associated with the given key.\n\n**Parameters:**\n\n- `key` - The key to look up\n\n**Returns:** The value associated with the key, or `undefined` if not found.\n\n### set(key, value)\n\nStores a value associated with the given key.\n\n**Parameters:**\n\n- `key` - The key to store the value under\n- `value` - The value to store\n\n**Returns:** The stored value.\n\n### delete(key)\n\nDeletes the value associated with the given key.\n\n**Parameters:**\n\n- `key` - The key to delete\n\n**Returns:** `true` if a value was deleted, `false` otherwise.\n\n### clear()\n\nRemoves all entries from the cache.\n\n**Returns:** `undefined`\n"}}],"model":"qwen/qwen3.5-9b","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":5366,"output_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":5266},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c03066ab-1d4c-45ea-bfbb-dfcbccc3b1da","uuid":"c058f7f8-e850-4769-9a55-0dc2321e8101","timestamp":"2026-07-21T23:31:47.070Z"}
